<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q44_v2" title="Q44_v2" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Un panel de corcho rectangular está formado por <m:math><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math> filas y <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> columnas de cuadrados idénticos de <m:math><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi></m:math> de lado. Se desea rodear completamente el borde del panel con una cinta decorativa.</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>¿Cuál de las siguientes afirmaciones sobre la cantidad de cinta necesaria para rodear el panel es correcta?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">Para rodear el panel se necesitan 2,4 m de cinta.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El panel mide 12 × 5 = 60 cm de largo y 8 × 5 = 40 cm de ancho. Su perímetro es 2 × (60 + 40) = 2 × 100 = 200 cm, que equivale a 2,0 m. Por lo tanto, no se necesitan 2,4 m.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">Para rodear el panel se necesitan 2,0 m de cinta.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! El panel mide 12 × 5 = 60 cm por 8 × 5 = 40 cm. Entonces, el perímetro es 2 × (60 + 40) = 200 cm. Como 200 cm = 2,0 m, la afirmación es verdadera.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">Para rodear el panel se necesitan 4,8 m de cinta.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El panel mide 60 cm por 40 cm, porque 12 × 5 = 60 y 8 × 5 = 40. El perímetro correcto es 2 × (60 + 40) = 200 cm = 2,0 m. Como 4,8 m corresponde a 480 cm y 480 ≠ 200, esa afirmación no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">Para rodear el panel se necesitan 0,96 m de cinta.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El panel tiene largo 60 cm y ancho 40 cm, ya que 12 × 5 = 60 y 8 × 5 = 40. Por eso, su perímetro es 2 × (60 + 40) = 200 cm = 2,0 m. En cambio, 0,96 m equivale a 96 cm, y 96 ≠ 200.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Determinar las dimensiones del panel</strong></p>
            <p>El panel tiene <m:math><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math> filas y <m:math><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:math> columnas de cuadrados de lado <m:math><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Largo del panel:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>cm</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Ancho del panel:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>cm</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, el panel mide <m:math><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi></m:math> por <m:math><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Calcular el perímetro del rectángulo</strong></p>
            <p>Para rodear completamente el borde se necesita el perímetro:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>40</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>200</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>cm</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Convertir a metros</strong></p>
            <p>Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, se tiene:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>200</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>cm</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La cantidad de cinta necesaria para rodear el panel es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>